----------------------------------
RELEASE NOTES FOR VERSION 0.1.149
----------------------------------
USER VISIBLE CHANGES
Automatic system recovery of running jobs after daemon failure has been added into 
the job queue eserver and the run-time daemon.  A flag to specify if the checkpoint 
file should be used is passed to the SPK computation driver. 

OTHER CHANGES
When the compilation process failed and a core dump was generated. The core dump 
was archived and placed into the production database.  This problem was fixed by 
making the compiler daemon not place cpp_source into the database when a core dump 
was generated.

